ENTRY            F0580   20251215   20260305   20260305       F105
SUBENT        F0580001   20251215   20260305   20260305       F105
BIB                 11         24
TITLE      The 12C(alpha,gamma)16O cross section at stellar
           energies
AUTHOR     (A.Redder,H.W.Becker,C.Rolfs,H.P.Trautvetter,
           T.R.Donoghue,T.C.Rinckel,J.W.Hammer,K.Langanke)
INSTITUTE  (2GERMST,2GERTHS,1USAOSU)
REFERENCE  (J,NP/A,462,385,1987)
FACILITY   (DYNAM,2GERTHS) 4MV Dynamitron
SAMPLE     The 12C targets were produced by ion implantation into
           gold layer, which had been evaporated onto a 2 mm thick
           Cu sheet (2x2 cm2 area).
DETECTOR   (NAICR) In the first experiment, 8 crystals were used
            (7 crystals - 10.2cm in diam. and 10.2cm thick,
           1 crystal with 12.7 in diam. and 12.7 cm thick).
           (GE-IN) In a second experiment, 6 germanium detectors
           of 12 to 35% efficiency were used.
           In the third experiment, 3 germanium detectors
           were used.
MONITOR    ((MONIT)6-C-12(A,G)8-O-16,PAR,SIG)
METHOD     (BCINT)
ERR-ANALYS (MONIT-ERR) Normalization error
HISTORY    (20010410C)
           (20080702A) Reference code was changed. Error
           definition was changed.
           (20251215U) SD: Small corrections in all Subents.
ENDBIB              24
COMMON               4          3
EN-NRM     E-LVL-NRM  MONIT      MONIT-ERR
MEV        MEV        NB         NB
  2.36       0.0       47.         4.
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           31
SUBENT        F0580002   20251215   20260305   20260305       F105
BIB                  5          9
REACTION   (6-C-12(A,G)8-O-16,PAR,SIG,,SFC)
FLAG       (1.) Obtained in the course of measurements of the
           absolute cross section
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-S) The errors assigned are predominantly
            statistical.
           (ERR-1) An overall error has to be added from
           uncertainties in the standard cross section.
STATUS     (TABLE,,A.Redder+,J,NP/A,462,385,1987) Tbl.1
HISTORY    (20251215U) SD: BIB updated. DATA-ERR -> ERR-1.
ENDBIB               9
COMMON               2          3
E-LVL      ERR-1
MEV        PER-CENT
  0.0         6.
ENDCOMMON            3
